---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Terms of Use — ApplianceErrors.com';
const description = 'Terms and conditions for using ApplianceErrors.com.';
const updated = '2026-06-10';
---
<BaseLayout {title} {description}>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 prose prose-gray">
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: {updated}</em></p>

    <p>
      By accessing ApplianceErrors.com ("the site") you agree to these terms.
      If you do not agree, please do not use the site.
    </p>

    <h2>1. Informational use only</h2>
    <p>
      All content on this site is provided for <strong>informational
      purposes only</strong>. It is not a substitute for professional advice
      from a licensed appliance technician, electrician, plumber, or gas
      engineer. Always consult your appliance's official service manual and
      follow the manufacturer's safety instructions.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Safety disclaimer</h2>
    <p>
      Home appliance repair can involve hazardous voltages, sharp components,
      high pressure water, refrigerant, and natural gas. You assume full
      responsibility for any repairs you attempt. Always:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Unplug the appliance and shut off water/gas before servicing.</li>
      <li>Use the correct tools and personal protective equipment.</li>
      <li>Stop immediately if you are unsure and call a licensed professional.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      ApplianceErrors.com, its operators, and contributors are not liable for
      any injury, property damage, data loss, or other harm arising from use
      of the information on this site.
    </p>

    <h2>3. No warranty</h2>
    <p>
      The site is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind, express or
      implied. We do not guarantee that the information is accurate, complete,
      current, or that the site will be uninterrupted or error-free.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Trademarks</h2>
    <p>
      Brand names (Samsung, LG, Whirlpool, GE, Bosch, etc.) and model numbers
      are trademarks of their respective owners. ApplianceErrors.com is not
      affiliated with, endorsed by, or sponsored by any appliance manufacturer.
      Trademarks are used for identification and reference only.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Affiliate disclosure</h2>
    <p>
      Some outbound links on this site are affiliate links. We may earn a
      commission on qualifying purchases, at no additional cost to you. See our
      <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a> for details.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>
      All site content — text, layout, design — is © ApplianceErrors.com unless
      otherwise stated. You may link to our pages freely. Reproduction of
      substantial portions without permission is not allowed.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms at any time. Continued use of the site after
      changes constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
    </p>

    <h2>8. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions: <a href="mailto:hello@applianceerrors.com">hello@applianceerrors.com</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
